17/03/2009
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Prime Minister Emil Boc presented a government plan to parliament on Monday (March 16th) aimed at blunting the impact of the global financial crisis. 
Boc stressed some of the measures would be top priorities for the cabinet, including investing in infrastructure, maintaining the current flat tax rate, and injecting capital into the Romanian Savings Bank and Eximbank. 
The plan also includes measures to protect the low-income population, including a programme to subsidise medicines for pensioners. 
(Cotidianul, Ziarul Financiar, Adevarul - 17/03/09; Ziare, NewsIn - 16/03/09)
